sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This plasmid allows bleomycin-selected cells to express the D5R dopamine receptor subunit upon induction with doxycycline.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM2008 Princeton team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PLV-TRE-IRES2-EGFP [BBa_I745000] was digested with EcoRI and BsrGI, which allowed the insertion of the PCR SOEd EcoRI-D5R-Ubc-Bleo-BsiWI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This plasmid was constructed by PCR SOEing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I745000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This backbone consists of the TRE promoter, activated when the reverse transactivator, rtTA, and Doxycycline together bind the promoter. An IRES (internal ribosomal binding site) follows the TRE promoter and EGFP follows the IRES.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Weiss Lab
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This plasmid was designed by the Weiss lab for use as a lentiviral vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We wanted to create a vector that could be modular and one that would allow one to use any promoter, any gene of interest and any selection/fluorescent marker. We designed the promoter with flanking PacI and EcoRI sites and the gene site with SfiI, EcoRI, BamHI and NheI sites. However, due to the lack of available sites in a lentivector, we had difficulty designing a modular IRES-indicator/selection fragment. Work is underway to correct this.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene encodes a specific subunit of a dopamine receptor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Available commercially
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Extracted from the source plasmid by PCR.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a stable constitutive promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Available
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was obtained from members of the Weiss Lab.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Using this promoter allows for the constant expression of a reporter gene or a selectable antibiotic.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene is an antibiotic that allows for the selection of cells containing any construct that includes it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Commercially available
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No backbone containing this gene was initially available. Using this gene enabled the construction of future Bleo-selectable plasmids.
